Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
hilite_proto_model(25.10)                            hilite_proto_model(25.10)

Name
       hilite_proto_model  -  Highlights  objects, such as, FlexModels, parti-
       tions, and/or power domains

Syntax
       hilite_proto_model

       [-help]

       [-keep_existing_hilite]

       [-type {flex_module flex_instgroup partition power_domain}]

        [-reset]

       [-level <integer>] | {[-min_level <integer>][-max_level <integer>]}

       Highlights objects, such as, FlexModels, partitions, and/or  power  do-
       mains.  This  command  automatically resets the list of used colors for
       each partition, so that the same color(s) can be re-used  in  different
       partitions.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -keep_existing_hilite
              Highlights  new  objects in addition to the existing highlighted
              objects.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -level <integer>
              Specifies the level to highlight.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -max_level <integer>
              Highlights objects from level 0 to the specified level.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -min_level <integer>
              Minimum level to highlight.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -reset Resets all the previously highlighted models.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type {flex_module flex_instgroup partition power_domain}
              Allows you to specify which model type(s) to be highlighted.

              Default: flex_module flex_instgroup

              Data_type: enum_list, optional

Examples
       The example below has the level range from 0 to 1. So we have min_level
       0 and max_level 1. Default hilite_proto_model works levels from min  to
       max.

       Before hilite_proto_model

       hilite_proto_model or <CMD>hilite_proto_model -min_level 0 -max_level 1

       or

       hilite_proto_model -min_level 0 #

       These three usages have the same result on this design.

       hilite_proto_model -level 1 #

       Only display FlexModels on the specified level.

       Or

       hilite_proto_model -min_level 1 #

       Display FlexModels upper or equal with level 1.

